<para id="fs-idm61093248"><newline/><emphasis effect="italics">Use the following information to answer the next four exercises:</emphasis> A baker is deciding how many batches of muffins to make to sell in his bakery. He wants to make enough to sell every one and no fewer. Through observation, the baker has established a probability distribution.</para><table id="fs-idm43289680" summary="A two column, five row table is shown. The header row contains the following column titles: x, and P opening parenthesis x closing parenthesis. The first data row contains 1 and 0.15. The second data row contains 2 and 0.35. The third data row contains 3 and 0.40. The final data row contains 4 and 0.10.">
